summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 23537 entitled: "An ordinance relating to and providing for the improvement of the alley in block 17, Boren, Denny & Yesler Addition being the alley from Spring Street to Seneca Street, and between 5th Avenue and 6th Avenue, all in the City of Seattle, by grading and paving the same with brick, all in accordance with Majority Petition No. 39555, of the city council of the City of Seattle; and providing payment therefor by the mode of "Payment in Bonds", as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle" approved March 16, 1910.
